article.description: Devon Goodman, AJ Brodeur and Jake Silpe scored all but five of Penn's points as the Quakers completed their first weekend sweep of the Ivy League season, defeating Brown 58-51 on Saturday night in the Palestra to claim the final berth in the league...
article.headline: Penn rallies in 2nd half tops Brown 58-51, makes Ivy tourney
article.linkText: Penn rallies in 2nd half tops Brown 58-51, makes Ivy tourney
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Devon Goodman, AJ Brodeur and Jake Silpe scored all but five of Penn's points as the Quakers completed their first weekend sweep of the Ivy League season, defeating Brown 58-51 on Saturday night in the Palestra to claim the final berth in the league tournament. Penn (19-11, 7-7) is defending champion in the Ivy League Tournament but needed to beat Brown in order to return. The Quakers scored eight unanswered points to open the second half, breaking a 27-27 halftime tie, and led the rest of the way. Brodeur scored two layups, Goodman and Max Rothschild added the other baskets in the game-changing burst. Rothschild scored just two points but added seven rebounds, four assists and three steals. Penn had a dozen steals as Brown committed 22 turnovers, resulting in 21 points for Penn. Desmond Cambridge led the Bears (19-11, 7-7) with 13 points. Joshua Howard and Tamenang Choh scored 10 apiece and Choh had nine rebounds. Brown was 17 of 50 shooting to Penn's 24 of 60. Penn defeat Yale 77-66 on Friday night.
